testcase.name: ArrayList should be of type List
ArrayList should be empty at the beginning
ArrayList should contain all elements that have been given in the constructor
ArrayList should contain one element when an element is added
ArrayList should add an element at the correct position
ArrayList should contain all added elements
ArrayList should fail if an element at an invalid position is requested
ArrayList should return an element that has been added
ArrayList should fail if an element at an invalid position should be inserted
ArrayList should be empty after clear has been called
ArrayList should return true if an element has been added and contains is called (and false otherwise)
ArrayList should be equal to another collection with the same elements
ArrayList should not be equal to another collection with the same elements in a different order
ArrayList should contain the correct elements if removeAll is called
ArrayList should return the correct values for indexOf and lastIndexOf
ArrayList should contain the correct elements if remove is called
ArrayList should retain the correct elements if retain is called
ArrayList should replace the correct element when set is called
ArrayList should return the correct elements when subList is called
